data.description: Nestled within the prestigious Sara Bay Country Club, this beautiful 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home offers a serene and inviting setting on a spacious 0.37-acre lot, overlooking the picturesque golf course. Situated in the desirable Whitfield-Ballentine Overlay District, the property enjoys a prime location.  Enter the home to a welcoming living room that flows seamlessly into the family room and kitchen, creating a spacious and open floor plan ideal for family gatherings or entertaining. The large master suite, measuring 19 x 19, features two walk-in his & her closets and an en-suite bathroom, while the third bedroom offers a walk-in closet and could easily serve as an office or den. The other secondary bedroom, or nursery, has its attached bathroom for the guests or kids.  Step outside onto the screened lanai and enjoy the stunning sunrise views over the golf course. The generous lot, part of which is currently fenced, provides ample space for a pool or outdoor living area and can easily be adapted to suit your needs.  Recent upgrades include a new roof in 2023, a new A/C unit and airhandler in 2022, new flooring, baseboards, fresh paint inside and out, updated ceiling fixtures in master bed, common areas, and more. A 24x24 garage accommodates two vehicles, and a circular driveway adds convenience and beautiful curb appeal.  Enhance your lifestyle with optional membership in the Whitfield Association and receive a culinary membership to Sara Bay Country Club, granting access to top-notch dining. Explore nearby attractions like the Ringling Art Museum, University of South Florida, Ringling School of Art, and Sarasota Airport, all within minutes of your doorstep. A nearby marina provides easy access to the Gulf of Mexico.  With its prime location, extensive updates, and abundant wildlife visitors, this home presents a unique opportunity for both families and vacationers alike. Experience the best of Sarasota living in this welcoming retreat! Don't miss a chance to see this hidden gem today!
